The Constitution of the Islamic Republic of Pakistan and the laws in force in the Province of the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa, the Police has an obligation to perform its duties and functions in an efficient manner for prevention and detection of crime and maintenance of public order and to maintain effective internal discipline, achieve high performance standards and ensure across the board service delivery, it is expedient to give operational, administrative and financial autonomy to Police and to reconstruct and regulate the Police in order to be responsible, service oriented and responsive to effectively uphold and enforce laws, maintain public order, protect the lives, properties and honour of the people, without any discrimination through modern proactive policing and community participation;


The aim objective of the Police Act is to make the police apolitical and accountable to the people through democratic institutions and civilian oversight bodies.


The Provincial Government established the Provincial Public Safety Commission, Capital City District Public Safety Commission and District Public Safety Commission under Section (48) (51) (53) of the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Police Act, 2017.
